    "content_hash": "af4eaa8049060050",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "SOFTWARE ENGINEER – DEVOPS\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation and growth drive everything we do. Our Engineering teams tackle complex technical challenges across a global, three-sided marketplace, building and scaling systems that serve millions of customers, riders and partners every day.\n\nFrom real-time logistics to resilient infrastructure and marketplace optimisation, we design, build and operate technology that powers Deliveroo’s growth at scale.\n\nWe’re looking for a Software Engineer – DevOps to join our London team. In this role, you’ll operate at the intersection of software engineering and cloud infrastructure to build the core systems that enable our global engineering organisation to ship software at scale. This role is based in our London office with a hybrid setup, typically 3 days in the office.\n\nGet to know our Engineering https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/software-engineering-at-deliveroo/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the Foundations team. We treat infrastructure, CI/CD and developer tooling as software products, engineered with the same care as customer-facing systems to increase velocity, reliability and security across Deliveroo.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Architect and automate infrastructure using Go to improve developer workflows and enhance platform capabilities.\n\n - Design and operate secure, scalable systems within AWS, balancing high performance with operational excellence.\n\n - Engineer robust CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions, CircleCI or Buildkite to streamline global deployment cycles.\n\n - Drive Infrastructure as Code (IaC) standards to ensure automated, repeatable environment management across the stack.\n\n - Enhance system reliability by troubleshooting complex production issues and improving observability across application and infrastructure layers.\n\n - Partner with engineering teams to define best practices for deployment, release management and cloud architecture.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nOur ideal candidate will bring strong expertise in some of these areas and curiosity to grow in others:\n\n - Strong experience building and operating CI/CD systems using tools such as GitHub Actions, CircleCI or Buildkite.\n\n - Experience writing and maintaining production-quality software, including proficiency in a language such as Go.\n\n - Solid AWS knowledge, including core services, networking, IAM and cloud-native architecture principles.\n\n - Proven ability to work with GitHub, including workflow automation and repository management.\n\n - Experience with infrastructure as code and automated environment management.\n\n - Strong understanding of reliability, observability and operational best practices.\n\n - Ability to debug complex systems and work effectively across multiple engineering teams.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters—solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Solve meaningful problems at real scale Work on a complex, always-on marketplace that impacts millions every day.\n\n🌱 See your impact, fast Ship, test and improve ideas quickly in a low-hierarchy, high-ownership environment.\n\n🧠 Grow through challenge and ownership Take on big, ambiguous problems and accelerate your career with strong support.\n\n🌎 A culture built for builders High standards, collaboration, flexible working and continuous learning.\n\n➡️ Want a deeper look at how we build? Check out our Tech Blog https://deliveroo.engineering.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Explore our Engineering Interview Guide here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/interview-guide-for-engineers/ to help you feel confident at each stage.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
